title: Bihar polls: ADR moves SC over revision of electoral rolls; calls EC move illegal

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Ciara supports Russell Wilson as his clothing label, 3BRAND, appears in Marvel's Ironheart. The brand made its TV debut in the Disney+ series. Wilson shared his excitement on social media. Ciara also expressed her pride. 3BRAND's appearance raises its profile in fashion and entertainment. The couple's business bond continues to grow. Their influence has now reached a global superhero stage.
title: Ciara celebrates Russell Wilson’s Marvel debut in style; sweet 3BRAND shoutout melts fans

author: TOI NEWS DESK
title: 'Fadnavis did what Balasaheb could not': Raj Thackeray at 'victory' rally with Uddhav

author: TNN
description: In Rajasthan's Bhilwara district, Sitaram Keer died after a road accident led to mob violence. The incident occurred in Jahazpur, triggering communal tensions. Hindu groups protested, and the VHP called for a Muharram procession ban. Police have been deployed, and three individuals are detained. An investigation is underway, and a temple event has been postponed.
title: Rajasthan shocker: Man beaten to death in Bhilwara; cops deployed, markets shut

author: TOI SCIENCE DESK
description: A groundbreaking study has unveiled a surprising truth about our perception of time: the present moment is not as straightforward as it seems. Our brains intricately delay and blend visual signals from the previous 15 seconds, creating a polished, uninterrupted experience that shields us from the sensory overload of reality.
title: Science uncovers visual illusion in mind: Your brain may be 15 seconds behind reality

author: KRISHNA CHAUDHARY
description: A 22-year-old student from Bihar has accused a madrassa teacher in Meerut of confinement, torture, and sexual assault over three years. The survivor reported being forced into three abortions by the teacher and his wife. Police have arrested the teacher and filed charges against him and his wife, initiating a thorough investigation into the serious allegations.
title: 'Got pregnant thrice': UP madrassa teacher held for sexually assaulting student for 3 yrs

author: ARANI BASU
description: Jamie Smith's explosive batting display at Edgbaston ignited the Barmy Army, overshadowing the Bharat Army's chants. Smith's counter-attacking century fueled England's fightback, prompting improvised songs and spirited exchanges between the rival fan groups. The Barmy Army's rediscovered voice echoed through the Eric Hollies stand, celebrating Smith's crucial innings and England's resurgence.
title: 2nd Test: Barmy Army roars as Jamie Smith silences Bharat Army at Edgbaston

author: TOI NEWS DESK
title: 'Hope to live 30-40 more years': Dalai Lama amid succession row

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Uddhav and Raj Thackeray united at a Mumbai rally, celebrating the withdrawal of the three-language policy GRs. Raj Thackeray criticized the BJP-led Mahayuti for imposing Hindi without discussion, emphasizing Marathi unity's strength. This rare joint appearance followed protests against making Hindi compulsory in schools, highlighting cultural unity over political differences after the government's decision reversal.
title: Language row: After 20 years, Thackeray brothers share stage at mega 'victory' rally

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: US President Donald Trump is set to send tariff letters to twelve countries starting Monday, with new reciprocal rates potentially effective from August 1, 2025. Trump’s letters will be sent with the American side indicating a ‘take it or leave it’ offers.
title: 'Take it or leave it': Trump says US tariff letters ready for 12 countries

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Entrepreneur Sushil Kedia faced backlash after his social media post about not learning Marathi despite living in Mumbai for 30 years. MNS workers vandalized Kedia's Mumbai office, prompting condemnation from BJP leaders. Kedia claimed he was being tracked by police under the guise of protection. The incident sparked debate about language pride and the limits of expression in Maharashtra.
title: Watch: MNS workers vandalise bizman's Mumbai office over post on Marathi

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Near the Chanderkot Langer site, five buses in a convoy of Amarnath pilgrims collided on the Jammu-Srinagar National Highway, resulting in minor injuries to 36 pilgrims. The incident occurred around 8 am as the buses traveled from Jammu to Pahalgam. Injured pilgrims received immediate medical attention at Ramban district hospital, and alternative transportation was arranged for their onward journey.
title: 36 Amarnath pilgrims injured after five buses collide in J&K's Ramban

author: TNN
title: 5 dead in Jharkhand illegal mine collapse, several feared trapped

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Chinese foreign minister Wang Yi reportedly told the EU that Beijing views a Russian defeat in Ukraine as unacceptable, fearing it would allow the US to concentrate on China. Despite China's official neutrality, Wang's comments suggest a preference for a prolonged conflict that keeps the US engaged.
title: Beijing says can't afford Russia losing in Ukraine, wants US distracted: Report

author: TNN
description: A Bengaluru civil engineer, Bhaskar, died after his wife, Shruthi, struck him with a wooden stick during a domestic dispute. Shruthi claims self-defense, alleging years of abuse and provocation after Bhaskar returned home intoxicated from an affair. The postmortem revealed blunt-force trauma. Shruthi is now in judicial custody, with police considering her claims.
title: B'luru horror: Drunk man dies in sleep after wife hits him with stick

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: D Gukesh triumphed in the SuperUnited Rapid & Blitz tournament's rapid section in Zagreb, highlighted by a victory against World No. 1 Magnus Carlsen. After an initial loss, Gukesh demonstrated resilience with five consecutive wins, securing his lead. He concluded the rapid section with a win against Wesley So and aims to maintain his form in the upcoming blitz format.
title: Chess | Gukesh reveals bet with cousin if he beat Carlsen; leads by 3 points in Zagreb

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Union Minister Kiren Rijiju and Arunachal Pradesh CM Pema Khandu attended the Dalai Lama's birthday celebrations in Dharamshala, following a dispute between China and India over his succession. China urged India to handle Tibet-related issues cautiously after Rijiju stated the Dalai Lama's reincarnation should be his own decision. The MEA clarified India's neutrality on the selection process, emphasizing religious freedom.
title: Watch: Rijiju attends Dalai Lama's b'day celebration; strong msg to China

author: VIJAYA TIWARI
description: Actress Yuvika Chaudhary, mother to baby Ekleen, balances motherhood and her career. Speaking to Times of India TV, she acknowledges the entertainment industry's challenges, highlighting her and husband Prince Narula's self-made success. Yuvika cherishes the unique atmosphere of being on set and misses reading long scripts.
title: Yuvika Chaudhary: 24 hours of my day are spent juggling between motherhood and work

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Mohammed Siraj's sensational six-wicket haul against England at Edgbaston was immortalized in a video showcasing his journey from humble beginnings to cricket stardom. His figures of 6/70 not only dented England’s top order but also etched his name in history as he joined the ranks of Indian bowling legends at the venue.
title: 'Brace yourself for Siraj storm': Video montage celebrates pacer’s spell | Watch

author: TANUJ LAKHINA
description: Tadej Pogacar, a strong contender after his Critérium du Dauphiné win, aims for his fourth Tour de France victory. Facing rivals like Jonas Vingegaard and Remco Evenepoel, Pogacar emphasises the importance of mental strength, nutrition, and teamwork in the demanding 21-stage race. He highlights the unique beauty and challenges of Grand Tours, fueled by his love for cycling.
title: Exclusive | 'They bring the best out of me' - Pogacar on rivalry with Vingegaard, Evenepoel

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Rahul Gandhi criticized PM Modi, anticipating he would yield to Trump's tariff deadline amid US trade talks. Piyush Goyal affirmed India's commitment to protecting its national interests, particularly for farmers and industries, during negotiations. While the US seeks tariff reductions on agricultural products, India aims for concessions in labor-intensive sectors like textiles and leather.
title: 'Modi will meekly bow': Rahul reacts to Piyush Goyal's US trade deal remark

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: In Lahore, Pakistan, a runaway pet lion attacked a woman and two children on a busy street, prompting a swift police response. The lion, escaping its enclosure, injured the victims before being captured and taken to a wildlife sanctuary. Authorities arrested three individuals in connection with the incident, highlighting ongoing concerns about exotic animal ownership in the region.
title: Caught on camera: Runaway pet lion attacks woman, kids in Lahore

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: During the India-England Test match, a lighthearted fashion contest emerged among the Sky Sports commentary team. Michael Atherton initiated the banter by criticising Nasser Hussain's casual attire, leading to a humorous awards ceremony. Ravi Shastri ultimately claimed the title of "Best Dressed Commentator" with his stylish white jacket, celebrated for its flair and confidence.
title: Cricket | Shastri, DK or Sanga? And the best dressed commentator goes to ...

author: etimes.in
description: In a recent vlog with Farah Khan, Munawar Faruqui candidly discussed his experiences, drawing a stark contrast between his time in jail and his Bigg Boss journey, emphasizing the incomparable nature of the two.
title: Farah Khan asks Munawar Faruqui to compare his jail term and Bigg Boss

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Al-Hilal players Ruben Neves and João Cancelo were inconsolable during the minute's silence for Diogo Jota and his brother Andre Silva who died in a car crash this week. During the FIFA Club World Cup quarter-finals, Chelsea's Pedro Neto paid tribute with a special shirt.
title: FIFA CWC: Neves, Cancelo break down; Neto carries special shirt in honour of Jota, Silva - watch

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Uddhav Thackeray and Raj Thackeray are set to share a stage after 20 years for a joint rally celebrating the withdrawal of government resolutions related to the three-language policy. The rally, organized by Shiv Sena (UBT) and MNS, marks a rare instance of unity between the cousins, focusing on Marathi language and identity.
title: Marathi cause reunites Thackeray brothers, to hold joint mega rally in Mumbai

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Patna police investigate the murder of businessman Gopal Khemka near Gandhi Maidan. He was shot dead. One bullet and shell were recovered. Earlier, two youths were also shot dead near a temple in Bikram. Police found an Apache motorcycle and twelve bullet shells at that scene. Authorities are investigating both incidents. Forensic teams are assisting in the Bikram case.
title: Patna bizman Gopal Khemka shot dead near Gandhi Maidan; bullet & shell recovered

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Tom Brady celebrated his mother Galynn's birthday on July 4th. He posted a heartfelt tribute on Instagram. He acknowledged her strength, especially during her cancer battle. Galynn was diagnosed in 2016. She attended Super Bowl LI in 2017. Brady also recognized her initial hesitation about his football career. He credited his parents for instilling important values.
title: Tom Brady’s Fourth of July tribute goes viral as he honors both America and his mother

author: DWAIPAYAN GHOSH
description: Manojit Mishra instructed a security guard to prepare a room before the law college gang rape. The guard, Pinaki Banerjee, was aware of parties in the room. He was threatened to remain silent. Other accused instructed Banerjee to leave his post. Police reconstructed the crime scene with the accused. They are investigating social media activity and Monojit's employment status.
title: Kolkata horror: 'Keep room ready', Monojit told guard before assault

author: TOI WORLD DESK
title: At least 13 dead in Texas flash floods; homes, vehicles swept away

author: RAUNAK BOSE
description: Golden State Warriors are making moves. They completed a seven-team trade involving Kevin Durant. Now, they might target Los Angeles Lakers' LeBron James. A trade could send Jimmy Butler to the Lakers. In return, Warriors would get James and his son, Bronny. Stephen Curry and James played well together in the Olympics. This potential duo could reshape the NBA.
title: Golden State Warriors could acquire Lakers superstar to form BIG 3 with Curry and Butler

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: A photo sparked rumours of LeBron James returning to Cleveland Cavaliers. James clarified he was simply training in his hometown. He remains committed to Los Angeles Lakers. He opted into his contract. The Lakers reshaped their roster. James' agent said he wants another championship. Insiders say the Cavaliers are not interested in a reunion. The Lakers aim for stability.
title: LeBron James responds after viral Cleveland Cavaliers' photo triggers Lakers exit rumors

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Pat Cummins's sensational caught-and-bowled dismissal of Keacy Carty highlighted a day dominated by bowlers in the second Test between Australia and West Indies. Cummins' athletic effort, described as world-class, removed Carty for 6. West Indies were restricted to 253, with Nathan Lyon taking 3 wickets, before Australia closed Day 2 on 12 for two.
title: Watch: Cummins defies gravity in stunning catch: 'Effort of the highest class'

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi's visit to Argentina marks the first bilateral visit by an Indian Prime Minister in 57 years, aiming to strengthen ties in areas like energy, critical minerals, and trade. Discussions with President Javier Milei will focus on cooperation in agriculture, mining, and renewable energy, with India eyeing Argentina's shale reserves and lithium resources for energy security.
title: Why PM Modi's Argentina trip is vital for India's clean energy ambitions

author: GITESH SHELKE AND ASSEEM SHAIKH
description: Pune police are investigating a rape allegation made by a 22-year-old data scientist against a supposed delivery agent. Commissioner Amitesh Kumar stated there was no forced entry or use of chemicals. The woman's friend, an IT professional, has been detained after his phone location placed him at the flat during the alleged incident.
title: Twist in Pune rape case: No forced entry, use of spray; selfie with consent

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Donald Trump, in a video released on July 4th, acknowledged his 2020 election defeat for the first time. The video, titled ‘Best life evolution video of President Donald J Trump,’ chronicles his life from childhood to his business and political career.
title: 2020 election loss, assassination attempt: Trump shares 'best life evolution' video - watch

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Mohammed Siraj etched his name in Indian cricket history, securing a remarkable 6/70 against England at Edgbaston. This feat places him among legends like Kapil Dev and Ishant Sharma. Siraj's performance is the best by an Indian at the ground since 1986.
title: IND v ENG: 'It's unbelievable' - Siraj joins Kapil in elite club with sensational spell

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Young India opener Yashasvi Jaiswal equaled Rahul Dravid and Virender Sehwag as the joint-fastest Indian to 2,000 Test runs, achieving the milestone in his 40th innings during the second Test against England. He also became the fastest Indian to the mark in terms of matches played, reaching it in 21 Tests.
title: IND v ENG: Jaiswal breaks Gavaskar’s 49-year record; joins elite list with Dravid & Sehwag

author: SIDHARTHA
description: Commerce minister Piyush Goyal anticipates record exports, driven by FTAs, despite global uncertainties. Investment is flowing into key sectors, with a focus on value-added and labor-intensive exports. The government is reviewing FTAs with Asean and Japan, while remaining cautious on trade relations with China, aiming for fair and balanced trade.
title: 'India has navigated uncertainty very well, exports may top $870bn': Piyush Goyal

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Aamir Khan and Genelia D'Souza's 'Sitaare Zameen Par,' released on June 20, 2025, continues its successful run, nearing ₹140 crore in domestic earnings after 15 days. Despite a minor drop on its second Friday, the film's occupancy rates improved, especially during evening and night shows. Aamir Khan expressed gratitude for the audience's warm reception and positive reviews.
title: 'Sitaare Zameen Par' day 15: Aamir Khan starrer sees a slight dip; inches closer to Rs 140 cr

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Sonakshi Sinha playfully addressed pregnancy rumors on July 4, 2025, sharing a humorous WhatsApp exchange with her husband, Zaheer Iqbal. She jokingly blamed Zaheer's constant offers of food for fueling the speculation about her weight gain. This isn't the first time Sonakshi has faced such rumors since her marriage in June 2024.
title: 'Stop feeding me!': Sonakshi Sinha blames Zaheer Iqbal for pregnancy rumours
